snippet: CVS Health will exclude 31 more prescription medicines from insurance coverage next year, including Viagra and treatments for diabetes and multiple sclerosis.
abstract: CVS Health unveils plans to exclude additional 31 prescription medicines, including Viagra, from insurance coverage in 2016.
lead_paragraph: CVS Health will exclude 31 more prescription medicines from insurance coverage next year, including Viagra and treatments for diabetes and multiple sclerosis.

headline.main: 31 Drugs, Including Viagra, Will Be Cut From CVS’s Formulary
